      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOLLIES (7) is a promising filly yet to miss the frame in two starts to date. Last appeared when she was successful over 1100m at Mackay on May 8. Has good early speed so should take up a forward position. Will play a major role in the outcome. SHAMOUTI (4) drifted back from her wide draw last start then hit the line hard to score by a nose at Gatton over 1100m. Worth following up. PHIL UP (1) tackled a turf track for the first time last start over today's course and distance, finishing 3.5 lengths from the winner in fourth. Open to big improvement and is worth following up. VIKING TREASURE (8) was heavily backed and justified the support when resuming last start over 1000m at Flinton, scoring by a neck. Will be better for that latest run and cannot be ruled out.",
